  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nCurrently, while we're waiting for a remote to send us the DAO fork block headers in order to determine if we're on the same side of the fork, we ignore any data requests they make. That seems to cause them treat us as a useless peer and disconnect.\r\n\r\nIt'd explain why when running on ropsten trinity can keep a high peer count but on mainnet most nodes disconnect shortly after the initial handshake.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nNeed to handle data requests while performing the DAO fork check. Or maybe keep ignoring them during the DAO fork check, but re-queue them once the check is completed\r\n",
