    "body": "Ideally we would want to perform the DAO fork check before adding the peer to the pool and letting the `ChainSyncer` handle its messages (e.g. reply to data requests), that's why I thought about having `peer.ensure_same_side_on_dao_fork()` re-adding the ignored messages to the queue, but since that runs before the peer has been added to the pool, there are no subscriber queue(s) to add those messages to. \r\n\r\nOne possible solution would be to have the `PeerPool.start_peer()` call `peer.ensure_same_side_on_dao_fork()` (changed to return the messages it ignored) because it can then re-add those messages to the subscribers at the same time it finally adds the peer to its list of connected nodes.",
